HEADWORD: Pinenchyma
<hw>Pi*nen"chy*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>pi`nax</grk> a tablet + <ets>-enchyma</ets>, as in
<ets>parenchyma</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Tabular parenchyma,
a form of cellular tissue in which the cells are broad and flat, as in
some kinds of epidermis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

